H0.text: The Dales Way is a path that runs from Bowness in Cumbria to which town in Yorkshire on the River Wharfe. Otley

H1.text: The Dales Way is a path that runs from Bowness in Cumbria to which town in Yorkshire on the River Wharfe. Skipton

H2.text: The Dales Way is a path that runs from Bowness in Cumbria to which town in Yorkshire on the River Wharfe. Harrogate

H3.text: The Dales Way is a path that runs from Bowness in Cumbria to which town in Yorkshire on the River Wharfe. Ilkley

A4.text: The Dales Way is an 78.5-mile (126.3 km) long-distance footpath in Northern England, from (south-east to north-west) Ilkley, West Yorkshire, to Bowness-on-Windermere, Cumbria.
